      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:26:8",
      "text": [
        " قَضَى أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) فِي رَجُلٍ كُسِرَ صُلْبُهُ فَلَا يَسْتَطِيعُ أَنْ يَجْلِسَ أَنَّ فِيهِ الدِّيَةَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from Abu Suleyman Al Hammar, from Bureyd Al Ajaly, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> judged regarding a man who broke his back, so he was not able to sit, that regarding it is the (complete) wergild’."
        ]
      }
